==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Frump
<hw>Frump</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[Cf. Prov. E.
<ets>frumple</ets> to wrinkle, ruffle, D. <ets>frommelen</ets>.]</ety>
<def>To insult; to flout; to mock; to snub.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Beau. & Fl.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Frump</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Frump
<hw>Frump</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A contemptuous speech or
piece of conduct; a gibe or flout.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Beau. & Fl.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A cross, old-fashioned person; esp., an old woman; a
gossip.</def> <mark>[Colloq.]</mark> <rj><au>Halliwell.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Frumper</ent>⟦br⟧
